pressing, you'll get a paste. Doing so makes for a smooth, flavorful addition to your vinaigrette, without chunks of garlic.\u003c/p\u003e","equipment":["8\" medium pot","baking sheet","10\" medium pan"],"id":2688,"ingredients":["white beans","cherry tomatoes","broccoli","lemon","yellow onion","orzo","crushed red pepper","garlic","sugar","grated Parmesan cheese"],"ingredients_full":[{"name":"white beans","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"cup","displayOrder":1,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/137/medium_square_white-beans-1.jpg"},{"name":"cherry tomatoes","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"pint","displayOrder":2,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/6/medium_square_cherry-tomatoes-test.jpg"},{"name":"broccoli","quantity":"12.0","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":3,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/219/medium_square_broccoli-2.jpg"},{"name":"lemon","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":4,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/16/medium_square_LEMON_SLICED_1_copy.jpg"},{"name":"yellow onion","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":5,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/27/medium_square_yellow-onion-test.jpg"},{"name":"orzo","quantity":"0.75","measurementUnit":"cup","displayOrder":6,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/218/medium_square_ORZO_-4559_copy.jpg"},{"name":"crushed red pepper","quantity":"0.5","measurementUnit":"teaspoon","displayOrder":7,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/39/medium_square_CRUSHED_RED_PEPPER_copy.jpg"},{"name":"garlic","quantity":"2.0","measurementUnit":"clove","displayOrder":8,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/2/medium_square_GARLIC_PEELED_copy.jpg"},{"name":"sugar","quantity":"0.5","measurementUnit":"teaspoon","displayOrder":9,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/292/medium_square_sugar-test.jpg"},{"name":"grated Parmesan cheese","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":10,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/22/medium_square_parmesan-cheese-2.jpg"}],"is_tastemaker":false,"upgradeable":false,"is_holiday_hack":false,"pantry_items":[],"pantry_items_full":[],"steps":[{"title":"Prepare Ingredients","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/22402/recipe_card_size_1._Prep_2X.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003ePreheat oven to 425°F. Bring a medium pot of water to a boil over high heat. Rinse \u003cstrong\u003ebeans\u003c/strong\u003e. Rinse remaining produce. Halve \u003cstrong\u003echerry tomatoes\u003c/strong\u003e. Halve \u003cstrong\u003ebroccoli\u003c/strong\u003e lengthwise, then cut lengthwise again into 1-inch florets with long stems. Discard any remaining stem, or peel and enjoy as a snack. Halve \u003cstrong\u003elemon\u003c/strong\u003e. Peel \u003cstrong\u003eonion\u003c/strong\u003e, halve and thinly slice.\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Cook Orzo","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/22403/recipe_card_size_2._Cook_orzo.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eSeason boiling water generously with \u003cstrong\u003esalt\u003c/strong\u003e. Stir in \u003cstrong\u003eorzo\u003c/strong\u003e and cook until al dente, about 12 minutes. Drain and set aside.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Char Broccoli and Make Garlic Paste","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/22404/recipe_card_size_3._Char_Broc.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eWhile orzo cooks, on a baking sheet, toss \u003cstrong\u003ebroccoli\u003c/strong\u003e with \u003cstrong\u003ecrushed red pepper \u003c/strong\u003e(skip or use half for less heat), \u003cstrong\u003e1 tablespoon olive oil\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003e.25 teaspoon salt\u003c/strong\u003e, and \u003cstrong\u003eblack pepper\u003c/strong\u003e. Roast until charred, 15 minutes. Meanwhile, on a cutting board, mince \u003cstrong\u003egarlic\u003c/strong\u003e and sprinkle over \u003cstrong\u003e.25 teaspoon salt\u003c/strong\u003e. Using a large knife, carefully scrape over mixture at a 45° angle, pressing down. Repeat until garlic is broken down (see Recipe Tip). \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Make Tomato Sugo","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/22405/recipe_card_size_4._Make_Sauce.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eHeat \u003cstrong\u003e1 tablespoon olive oil \u003c/strong\u003ein a medium pan over medium heat. When oil is shimmering, add \u003cstrong\u003eonion\u003c/strong\u003e and cook until beginning to soften, about 4 minutes. Add \u003cstrong\u003esugar\u003c/strong\u003e,\u003cstrong\u003e tomatoes\u003c/strong\u003e, and \u003cstrong\u003ehalf of garlic paste\u003c/strong\u003e,\u003cstrong\u003e \u003c/strong\u003eand cook, breaking up, until very soft, 4 minutes more. Add \u003cstrong\u003ebeans\u003c/strong\u003e and \u003cstrong\u003e2 tablespoons water\u003c/strong\u003e and simmer until sauce is thickened, 2-3 minutes more. Season with \u003cstrong\u003e.5 teaspoon salt \u003c/strong\u003eand \u003cstrong\u003eblack pepper\u003c/strong\u003e as desired. Remove pan from heat and set aside until Step 6.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Make Vinaigrette","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/22406/recipe_card_size_5._Make_Dressing.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eWhile sugo cooks, in a medium bowl, combine \u003cstrong\u003ejuice of 1 lemon\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003ehalf of Parmesan\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003eremaining garlic paste\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003e.25 teaspoon\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003esalt\u003c/strong\u003e, and \u003cstrong\u003eblack pepper\u003c/strong\u003e as desired. Whisk in\u003cstrong\u003e 2 tablespoons olive oil\u003c/strong\u003e until fully combined. Set aside.\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Finish Orzo and Plate","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/22407/recipe_card_size_6._Plate.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eOnce broccoli is roasted, return pan with tomato sauce to medium heat and add \u003cstrong\u003eorzo\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003eremaining Parmesan\u003c/strong\u003e, and \u003cstrong\u003e1 tablespoon olive oil\u003c/strong\u003e. Stir to coat \u003cstrong\u003eorzo\u003c/strong\u003e, 1-2 minutes. Taste and add more\u003cstrong\u003e salt \u003c/strong\u003eand \u003cstrong\u003eblack pepper\u003c/strong\u003e as desired, then divide between shallow serving bowls. Top \u003cstrong\u003eorzo \u003c/strong\u003ewith \u003cstrong\u003echarred broccoli\u003c/strong\u003e and drizzle over \u003cstrong\u003eParmesan vinaigrette\u003c/strong\u003e. Dig in!\u003c/p\u003e"}],"tags":{"all":[{"name":"vegetarian","slug":"vegetarian","hex_color":""}],"allergens":[{"name":"Milk","slug":"milk","hex_color":""},{"name":"Wheat","slug":"wheat","hex_color":""}],"proteins":[{"name":"vegetarian","slug":"vegetarian","hex_color":""},{"name":"Pasta","slug":"pasta","hex_color":""}],"publicFacing":[{"name":"vegetarian","slug":"vegetarian","hex_color":""}],"feature":[]}}